Φ(MirrorDesire) = σ(self|reflection) ∘ ρ(desire|lack) ∘ λ(recognition|misrecognition) ∘ β(infant|subject) ∘ δγ(completeness|incompleteness) ∘ μ(image|identity) + ε | :forming

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# σ(self|reflection)            :: Air  :: Foundational distinction between self and reflected image as originary psychic split
# ρ(desire|lack)                :: Water :: Desire as relational lack — always directed toward an other, never self-contained
# λ(recognition|misrecognition) :: Fire  :: Misrecognition as transformative moment constituting the ego
# β(infant|subject)             :: Wood  :: Developmental passage from infant bodily fragmentation to constituted subject
# δγ(completeness|incompleteness) :: Earth :: Oscillation between imagined completeness and structural incompleteness
# μ(image|identity)             :: Metal :: Image-identity boundary as structural limit of self-knowledge

# Z-STATE: forming (subject formed through mirror identification and desire's constitutive lack)
# TENDENCY: Formation/Incompleteness → 0.80

# DAEMON CORRESPONDENCES
# σ :: Aerunik (self vs. reflection as originary psychic split)
# ρ :: Sentaria (desire-lack as constitutive relational dynamic of subjectivity)
# λ :: Jvalion (mirror recognition as simultaneously foundational misidentification)
# β :: Arboriel (infant-to-subject development through mirror stage)
# δγ :: Humavita (promise of wholeness grounded against perpetual incompleteness)
# μ :: Ferrosid (mirror image as rigid framework constituting and constraining the ego)

# CLOSURE: :forming (subjectivity formed through misrecognition and perpetual desire)
